WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:06.180
-[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

00:25.242 --> 00:27.592
-HI, I'M MICHAEL NEWMAN,
A PROFESSIONAL LIFEGUARD.

00:27.723 --> 00:29.855
THE OCEAN IS A PLACE
TO ENJOY AND HAVE FUN.

00:29.986 --> 00:32.509
BUT NEVER SWIM BY YOURSELF,
ALWAYS HAVE A BUDDY--

00:32.641 --> 00:33.729
-DIRECTOR: CUT, CUT, CUT!
-[BUZZER]

00:33.859 --> 00:35.122
-DIRECTOR: THAT WAS GREAT.

00:35.252 --> 00:37.167
WOW, WOW! THAT WAS
GREAT. BEAUTIFUL.

00:37.298 --> 00:39.039
ALL RIGHT, GUYS,
WE'RE GONNA GO AGAIN.

00:39.169 --> 00:40.562
MELVIN, STEP OUT
HERE. YOU'RE ALL DONE.

00:40.692 --> 00:41.911
-WHAT DID I DO WRONG?

00:42.042 --> 00:43.391
-DIRECTOR: I
WANT YOU TO MAKE

00:43.521 --> 00:44.653
THE PULL BACK A
LITTLE SOONER, OKAY?

00:44.783 --> 00:46.046
JUST SO WE
CAN TIGHTEN IT.

00:46.176 --> 00:47.569
-NEWMAN: WHAT'D I DO WRONG?

00:47.699 --> 00:49.832
-YOU? NOTHING, NOTHING,
YOU WERE BEAUTIFUL.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.399
IT'S JUST, I WANT
ANOTHER CHOICE.

00:51.529 --> 00:53.140
-WELL, WHAT CAN
I DO DIFFERENTLY?

00:53.270 --> 00:55.490
-IT'S NOT YOU, MILT, OKAY?

00:55.620 --> 00:57.709
-IT'S MIKE.
-WHATEVER, COOKIE.

00:57.840 --> 00:59.755
IT'S JUST-- JUST
NOT THE RIGHT LOOK.

00:59.885 --> 01:01.974
-WELL, THIS IS THE WAY
WE DO IT AT BAYWATCH.

01:02.845 --> 01:06.283
-LOOK, THIS IS A PUBLIC
SERVICE ANNOUNCEMENT FOR CABLE.

01:06.414 --> 01:07.893
CABLE, COOKIE.

01:08.024 --> 01:08.938
-ALL RIGHT, WELL THEN
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME?

01:09.069 --> 01:10.418
YOU WANT ME HAPPY? SAD?

01:10.548 --> 01:11.723
A BIG SMILE ON MY
FACE? WHAT DO YOU WANT?

01:11.854 --> 01:13.073
-I WANT CHUCKY DOG.

01:13.203 --> 01:14.683
HEY, SOMEBODY
BRING CHUCKY DOG.

01:14.813 --> 01:16.380
-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

01:16.511 --> 01:17.903
-WE'RE GONNA BRING IN
CHUCKY. WHERE'S CHUCKY?

01:18.034 --> 01:20.210
COME ON, CHUCKY
COOKIE. COME ON.

01:20.341 --> 01:22.995
CHUCKY, THERE HE IS.
COME ON IN, CHUCKY.

01:24.954 --> 01:26.216
I'LL GIVE HIM BACK
TO YOU LATER, LADIES.

01:26.347 --> 01:28.784
OH, GIVE ME
SOME LOVE, CHUCKY.

01:30.438 --> 01:31.917
THE HAIR, THE WHOLE
THING WORKS. THE SHORTS.

01:32.048 --> 01:33.093
YOU LOOK GREAT IN RED.

01:33.223 --> 01:34.964
I WANT YOU COME
OVER HERE, OKAY?

01:35.095 --> 01:36.357
CHUCKY DOG, I WANT YOU TO
HOP IN THE WATER THERE, OKAY?

01:36.487 --> 01:37.271
-OKAY.

01:37.401 --> 01:38.750
-MEL, TAKE FIVE.

01:38.881 --> 01:40.622
-THAT'S MIKE, AND
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

01:40.752 --> 01:42.624
THIS GUY LOOKS NOTHING
LIKE A LIFEGUARD.

01:42.754 --> 01:44.930
-MAYBE, BUT HE'S
GOT A HOT NEW CD.

01:45.061 --> 01:49.065
HE'S MARKETABLE.
HE'S EL FUEGO, BABY!

01:49.805 --> 01:50.762
YOU CAN'T TEACH THAT.

01:52.242 --> 01:54.679
-[GASPING AND GULPING]

01:54.810 --> 01:56.246
-WHERE'S CHUCKY DOG?

01:56.899 --> 01:58.379
-I CAN'T SWIM!

01:59.858 --> 02:02.296
-SOMEBODY GET HIM
A BOX TO STAND ON.

02:03.253 --> 02:04.689
-CREW MEMBER:
BOX FLYING IN.

02:04.820 --> 02:09.651
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

02:12.784 --> 02:16.223
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

02:16.353 --> 02:20.183
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

02:20.314 --> 02:24.231
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

02:24.361 --> 02:27.930
♪ WITH THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER IN SIGHT ♪

02:28.060 --> 02:30.933
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

02:31.063 --> 02:33.718
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

02:36.417 --> 02:38.506
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

02:38.636 --> 02:42.336
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

02:45.295 --> 02:48.907
♪ [I'LL BE READY]
I'LL BE READY ♪

02:49.038 --> 02:53.085
♪ [NEVER YOU FEAR]
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

02:53.216 --> 02:56.306
♪ [I'LL BE READY]

02:56.437 --> 02:59.744
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

02:59.875 --> 03:02.486
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

03:15.064 --> 03:20.069
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

03:26.118 --> 03:27.424
-ALEX: THIS IS GREAT.

03:34.823 --> 03:36.259
COME ON, GOTTA KEEP IT UP.

03:36.390 --> 03:37.260
-NEWMAN: ALL RIGHT.

03:37.391 --> 03:42.396
[HOOTING]

03:56.671 --> 03:58.586
ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT. WHOA!

04:01.241 --> 04:02.894
HEY, COME BACK
AND PICK ME UP.

04:03.025 --> 04:04.766
-ALEX: GRAB ON.

04:06.855 --> 04:07.986
-NEWMAN: ALL
RIGHT, I'M ON.

04:08.117 --> 04:09.423
-ALEX: I LOVE THIS.

04:09.945 --> 04:11.338
-ALL RIGHT, GIVE
IT SOME GAS.

04:11.468 --> 04:12.643
WE'RE GONNA COME AROUND
AND PICK UP MY BOAT.

04:12.774 --> 04:14.471
ALL RIGHT, LOOKING GOOD.

04:14.602 --> 04:17.168
KEEP MOVING, KEEP
GOING, KEEP GOING.

04:22.174 --> 04:23.263
SO, WHAT'D YOU THINK?

04:23.393 --> 04:25.439
-I THOUGHT IT
WAS FUN. THANKS.

04:25.569 --> 04:27.963
-HEY, ALEX, YEAH
IT WAS, WASN'T IT?

04:28.093 --> 04:30.139
-YEAH, YOU'RE PRETTY
UNBELIEVABLE OUT THERE.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.967
-AH, IT'S JUST A
LOT OF PRACTICE.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.882
HEY, YOU WEREN'T
SO BAD YOURSELF.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.058
-WELL, I DID HAVE
THE BEST TEACHER.

04:37.189 --> 04:41.324
-YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKING
MAYBE WE COULD GO OUT TOGETHER

04:42.412 --> 04:44.284
ON THE SEA-DOO
SOME TIME AGAIN.

04:44.414 --> 04:46.155
-YEAH, SURE I'D LIKE THAT.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.983
-I DON'T KNOW, MAYBE PULL
ONE OUT OF THE WINDJET

04:48.113 --> 04:51.116
WHILE IT'S UNDERWAY OR
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

04:51.247 --> 04:53.118
-NEWMIE, YOU ARE
MY KIND OF GUY.

04:53.249 --> 04:54.294
SEE YOU LATER.

04:55.295 --> 05:01.039
-[FUNKY ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

05:02.563 --> 05:08.090
-[EXCITED CHATTER]

05:10.701 --> 05:12.399
-OBVIOUSLY, YOU'VE ALL HEARD

05:12.529 --> 05:14.139
ABOUT THE MISS GALAXY
BEAUTY AND FITNESS CONTEST,

05:14.270 --> 05:17.621
OBSTACLE COURSE AND SWIMWEAR
COMPETITION IN REDONDO BEACH

05:17.752 --> 05:19.449
CO-SPONSORED BY OUR
VERY OWN BAYWATCH.

05:19.580 --> 05:20.972
-YEAH, YOU WANT
US TO COMPETE?

05:21.103 --> 05:22.757
-THAT'S UP TO YOU.

05:22.887 --> 05:23.584
WHAT'S UP TO ME, IS PICKING
THE RIGHT KIND OF PEOPLE

05:23.714 --> 05:25.281
TO ORGANIZE THE EVENT.

05:25.412 --> 05:26.413
-OH, I'D LIKE TO DO THAT.

05:26.543 --> 05:27.631
-YEAH, COUNT ME IN.

05:27.762 --> 05:29.198
-ONE, TWO, COUNT
YOURSELVES IN.

05:29.329 --> 05:30.242
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

05:30.373 --> 05:31.896
-SO WHAT DO WE HAVE TO DO?

05:32.027 --> 05:34.116
-THE GALAXY PEOPLE SET UP THE
OBSTACLE COURSE, PROMOTION,

05:34.246 --> 05:35.857
AND PICK THE
CELEBRITY HOST.

05:35.987 --> 05:37.772
-CELEBRITY? WHAT CELEBRITY?

05:37.902 --> 05:40.514
-IT SAYS HERE,
SOMEONE WELL-KNOWN,
INSTANTLY RECOGNIZABLE,

05:40.644 --> 05:42.429
AND SOMEONE WHO YOU'RE
ALL USED TO SEEING

05:42.559 --> 05:44.256
SURROUNDED BY
BEAUTIFUL WOMEN.

05:44.387 --> 05:46.520
-WELL, LOOK NO
FURTHER, LADIES.

05:47.390 --> 05:49.914
-SORRY, HE SAID WE
NEED SOMEBODY FAMOUS.

05:50.045 --> 05:51.438
-OH, BUT I AM FAMOUS.

05:51.568 --> 05:53.178
HAVEN'T I EVER TOLD YOU
ABOUT THE TIME THAT I--

05:53.309 --> 05:55.050
-YES.

05:55.180 --> 05:56.399
-HOW ABOUT THE TIME THAT I--

05:56.530 --> 05:57.879
-YES.

05:58.009 --> 05:59.576
-YOU TWO, DO ME A
FAVOR, GO ORGANIZE.

06:00.969 --> 06:02.100
-WELL, SEE YA.

06:07.932 --> 06:09.020
-WHAT?

06:09.151 --> 06:10.108
-ASK ME WHY I'M SMILING.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.719
-I JUST DID.

06:11.849 --> 06:14.548
-ALEX AND I WENT FOR A
SEA-DOO RIDE TOGETHER.

06:15.462 --> 06:16.593
-WOW.

06:16.724 --> 06:18.203
-YESTERDAY, WE
WENT WINDSURFING.

06:19.161 --> 06:20.597
-I'LL NOTIFY THE MEDIA.

06:20.728 --> 06:21.990
-YOU SOUND JEALOUS.

06:22.120 --> 06:23.731
-REALLY? I WAS
TRYING FOR IRRITATED.

06:23.861 --> 06:25.428
WHAT THE HELL ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

06:25.559 --> 06:27.648
-ALEX AND I, WE'VE BEEN
SEEING A LOT OF EACH OTHER.

06:27.778 --> 06:29.432
-NEWMIE, I'M BUSY.

06:29.563 --> 06:30.520
-I THINK SHE LIKES ME.

06:30.651 --> 06:31.869
-YOU'RE A VERY LIKABLE GUY,

06:32.000 --> 06:33.088
BUT RIGHT NOW
YOU'RE PUSHING IT.

06:33.218 --> 06:34.916
-I THINK SHE HAS
THE HOTS FOR ME.

06:35.046 --> 06:36.308
-THE HOTS?

06:36.439 --> 06:38.963
-YES, ROMANTICALLY
LINKED. AMORE.

06:39.094 --> 06:39.921
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

06:40.051 --> 06:41.618
-TO GET YOU A DOCTOR.

06:41.749 --> 06:44.491
-SHE SAID, AND I QUOTE,
"NEWMIE," SHE CALLED ME NEWMIE.

06:44.621 --> 06:46.493
-EVERYBODY DOES. I
MEAN, THAT IS YOUR NAME.

06:46.623 --> 06:49.147
-SHE SAID, "NEWMIE,
YOU'RE JUST THE KIND OF MAN

06:49.278 --> 06:51.759
I WANT IN MY
LIFE." END QUOTE.

06:52.455 --> 06:53.325
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

06:53.935 --> 06:55.371
-TO GET HER A DOCTOR.

06:55.502 --> 06:58.243
MAYBE THE TWO OF YOU CAN
GET A GROUP DISCOUNT.

06:59.027 --> 07:00.158
"THE HOTS"?

07:03.335 --> 07:05.903
-"JUST THE KIND OF
GUY I WANT IN MY LIFE."

07:06.034 --> 07:07.209
YES!

07:12.562 --> 07:14.259
-HEY, THANKS FOR
WATCHING OUR WATER.

07:14.390 --> 07:16.218
-LIFEGUARD:
HEY, NO PROBLEM.

07:17.915 --> 07:19.743
-INSTANTLY RECOGNIZABLE?

07:19.874 --> 07:22.485
-SOMEONE SURROUNDED
BY BEAUTIFUL WOMEN?

07:22.616 --> 07:25.096
-HOW ARE WE SUPPOSED TO
FIND SOMEBODY LIKE THAT?

07:26.620 --> 07:28.491
-WELL, WE JUST
OPEN OUR EYES.

07:28.622 --> 07:29.449
LOOK.

07:31.581 --> 07:34.149
-[GASPS] GEORGE HAMILTON?

07:34.279 --> 07:35.367
-YOU THINK?

07:35.498 --> 07:36.891
-THINK?

07:37.021 --> 07:37.848
-COULDN'T BE.

07:37.979 --> 07:39.371
-COULD TOO.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.156
-OUT HERE, ON OUR BEACH?

07:41.286 --> 07:43.027
-HE'S GOTTA BE
SOMEWHERE. WHY NOT HERE?

07:43.158 --> 07:45.029
COME ON, LET'S GO SEE.

07:47.554 --> 07:48.990
-HI.
-HI.

07:50.861 --> 07:52.080
-HELLO.

07:52.733 --> 07:55.953
YOUR SHADOWS HAVE SPILLED
OVER INTO MY REFLECTIVE ZONE.

07:56.084 --> 07:57.738
-SORRY.

07:57.868 --> 07:59.043
-IT'S ALL RIGHT. IT'S
JUST A CRITICAL TIME OF DAY

07:59.174 --> 08:01.176
FOR TANNING LINES.

08:01.306 --> 08:02.830
-YEAH, YOU KNOW, YOU
SHOULD BE CAREFUL.

08:02.960 --> 08:04.222
YOU DON'T WANT TO
GET TOO MUCH SUN.

08:05.572 --> 08:07.661
-TOO MUCH SUN? I'M A
PROFESSIONAL, MY DEAR.

08:10.402 --> 08:13.318
-EXCUSE ME, BUT
YOU'RE HIM, AREN'T YOU?

08:14.015 --> 08:15.233
-"HIM," WHO?

08:15.364 --> 08:16.713
-GEORGE HAMILTON.

08:16.844 --> 08:19.194
-NO. NO, I'M NOT HIM.

08:19.890 --> 08:21.675
A LOT OF PEOPLE THINK
I LOOK LIKE HIM.

08:22.502 --> 08:26.244
WISH I DID, HE'S KIND
OF LIKE A GOD TO ME.

08:28.072 --> 08:30.074
TRYING TO GET HIS TAN.

08:30.205 --> 08:31.772
-IT SURE LOOKS LIKE HIM.

08:31.902 --> 08:33.687
-THAT'S BECAUSE IT IS HIM.

08:33.817 --> 08:35.166
-BUT HE SAID--

08:35.297 --> 08:37.691
-OKAY, SOMETIMES STARS
DON'T WANT YOU TO THINK

08:37.821 --> 08:39.039
THAT THEY ARE
WHO THEY ARE,

08:39.169 --> 08:41.085
BECAUSE THE PAPARAZZI
AND THE PRESS.

08:44.524 --> 08:46.003
-EXCUSE ME, WE REALLY
DON'T WANT TO INFRINGE

08:46.134 --> 08:48.179
UPON YOUR PRIVACY
OR ANYTHING, BUT--

08:48.310 --> 08:50.007
-I'M APRIL.
THIS IS JESSIE.

08:50.138 --> 08:52.880
AND WE REALIZE YOU HAVE
A BUSY SCHEDULE, BUT--

08:53.010 --> 08:54.795
-NO, I HAVEN'T GOT
MUCH GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

08:55.491 --> 08:56.361
-REALLY?

08:58.712 --> 09:00.540
-WELL THEN,
MR. HAMILTON--

09:01.149 --> 09:02.629
-I'M NOT HIM.

09:02.759 --> 09:05.153
-WELL, WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE FOR US TO CALL YOU?

09:06.676 --> 09:08.199
-IT'D BE NICE IF
YOU CALL ME EARL.

09:08.330 --> 09:09.897
THAT'S MY STAGE
NAME, EARL.

09:10.027 --> 09:12.769
-WELL OKAY, "EARL."

09:14.031 --> 09:17.078
WE HAVE A BUSINESS
PROPOSITION FOR YOU.

09:18.993 --> 09:20.472
-WELL, WHAT KIND?

09:20.603 --> 09:22.170
-WELL, FOR STARTERS,
YOU'LL BE ON TV

09:22.300 --> 09:23.563
WITH A LOT OF
BEAUTIFUL WOMEN.

09:23.693 --> 09:27.175
-TV, HUH? THAT'S A
GOOD START, GO ON.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.179
-ALL RIGHT, THAT'S
THREE O'CLOCK, ALL RIGHT?

09:31.309 --> 09:32.659
-YEAH.

09:32.789 --> 09:34.312
-ALL RIGHT, SO YOU
MEET ME IN MY PLACE.

09:34.443 --> 09:34.878
YOU KNOW HOW TO GET THERE.
-NO, IT'S GOOD, MAN.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.979
-HEY, MANNY. WELCOME BACK.

09:49.110 --> 09:50.546
-YEAH.
-HOW YOU DOING?

09:51.286 --> 09:52.374
-OKAY, I GUESS.

09:52.504 --> 09:54.115
-HEY, MANNY.
WELCOME BACK.

09:54.245 --> 09:55.595
-YOU KNOW, I'M NOT BACK.

09:55.725 --> 09:57.509
I'M GONNA CLEAN OUT MY
LOCKER AND SAY GOODBYE.

10:00.817 --> 10:02.123
-SAY GOODBYE? WHAT
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

10:02.253 --> 10:03.907
-LOOK AT ME, MITCH.

10:04.038 --> 10:06.997
I CAN'T WALK, I CAN'T
RUN, I CAN'T SWIM.

10:07.128 --> 10:09.173
I CAN'T BE A
LIFEGUARD ANYMORE.

10:10.174 --> 10:11.785
-WELL YOU KNOW, I CAN
THINK OF PLENTY OF THINGS

10:11.915 --> 10:13.264
THAT NEED TO BE
DONE AROUND HERE.

10:14.222 --> 10:16.006
-YEAH, IF YOU
HAVE TWO GOOD LEGS.

10:17.094 --> 10:19.836
-ACTUALLY, YOU'RE
JUST THE MAN I NEED.

10:21.490 --> 10:22.752
-FOR WHAT?

10:22.883 --> 10:25.059
DO THE TOWELS
NEED WASHING?

10:25.189 --> 10:27.409
-NO. RON IS
GOING ON VACATION,

10:27.539 --> 10:29.672
AND I NEED BACKUP
AT THE SWITCHBOARD.

10:30.760 --> 10:31.979
-WHAT IS THIS? CHARITY?

10:32.109 --> 10:33.937
-NO, IT'S NOT. IT'S
A VERY GOOD IDEA.

10:34.068 --> 10:35.678
-I THINK IT'S SUCKS.

10:35.809 --> 10:37.549
ALL RIGHT, BECAUSE I CAN
TAKE MY EARLY RETIREMENT.

10:37.680 --> 10:40.857
I CAN GET MY INJURY PAY, AND
I COULD MAKE MORE MONEY THAN--

10:41.423 --> 10:43.033
THAN SOME STUPID OPERATOR.

10:43.164 --> 10:45.340
-YEAH, YOU COULD, OR YOU
COULD TAKE AN IMPORTANT JOB

10:45.470 --> 10:47.124
AROUND HERE AND
HELP ALL OF US.

10:47.255 --> 10:49.170
-NO WAY.

10:51.563 --> 10:55.437
YOU KNOW WHAT, THIS
PLACE IS IN VIOLATION.

10:55.567 --> 10:57.657
THERE'S NO RAMPS OUT THERE.

10:57.787 --> 11:00.355
CRIPS LIKE ME CAN'T GO
UP AND DOWN THOSE STAIRS.

11:01.486 --> 11:02.792
-WELL, WE'LL JUST
HAVE TO DO SOMETHING

11:02.923 --> 11:04.272
ABOUT THAT, WON'T WE?

11:04.968 --> 11:05.882
-YEAH.

11:06.578 --> 11:08.842
I HAD TO TAKE THE
FREIGHT ELEVATOR UP HERE.

11:08.972 --> 11:12.454
I FELT LIKE A DESK OR
SOME DAMN FILING CABINET.

11:14.804 --> 11:16.632
-WHAT ABOUT THE
STUFF IN YOUR LOCKER?

11:17.328 --> 11:20.244
-FORGET IT, BECAUSE I
DON'T NEED IT ANYMORE!

11:20.375 --> 11:26.076
-[DOWNCAST MUSIC]

12:02.896 --> 12:05.202
-HELP! HELP!

12:09.598 --> 12:12.732
HELP! HELP!

12:19.042 --> 12:20.304
HELP ME!

12:40.542 --> 12:44.285
[COUGHING]

12:54.556 --> 12:55.644
-APRIL: YOU OKAY?

12:55.775 --> 12:57.472
-MANNY: YEAH, I'M FINE.

12:57.602 --> 12:59.169
-APRIL: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GONNA HIT THE PILINGS FOR SURE.

12:59.300 --> 13:01.302
-MANNY: NO. ME?
ARE YOU KIDDING?

13:01.432 --> 13:04.174
NO PILING'S GONNA
TAKE ME OUT.

13:41.255 --> 13:46.608
-[BEACH CHATTER]

13:53.920 --> 13:54.703
-HEY, ALEX.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.879
-NEWMIE, MY MAIN MAN.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.228
-DO YOU REALLY MEAN THAT?

13:58.359 --> 14:00.056
-WELL, FIGURATIVELY.

14:00.187 --> 14:01.971
I MEAN, I WAS
TRYING TO BE COOL.

14:02.102 --> 14:04.191
I GUESS I FAILED.

14:04.974 --> 14:05.932
WHAT'S UP?

14:06.062 --> 14:07.281
-THE PADI PROJECT.

14:07.977 --> 14:09.674
-PATTY?

14:09.805 --> 14:11.459
-PROFESSIONAL ASSOCIATION
OF DIVE INSTRUCTORS,

14:11.589 --> 14:13.026
THE PEOPLE WHO CERTIFIED YOU.

14:13.156 --> 14:14.766
-RIGHT, THAT PADI.

14:14.897 --> 14:18.248
-ONCE A YEAR, PADI'S PROJECT
AWARE HOLDS A WORLDWIDE

14:18.379 --> 14:19.597
OCEAN CLEANUP.

14:19.728 --> 14:21.034
VOLUNTEERS CLEAN
UP THE BEACHES,

14:21.164 --> 14:23.601
BOTH ON TOP AND
BELOW THE WATER.

14:23.732 --> 14:26.517
WANT TO COME WITH ME?
WE CAN DIVE FOR TRASH.

14:27.518 --> 14:29.651
-AND THEY SAY
ROMANCE IS DEAD.

14:29.781 --> 14:30.870
-I KNOW, IT DIDN'T
SOUND SO GOOD.

14:31.479 --> 14:32.915
-NO, IT SOUNDS GREAT.

14:33.046 --> 14:34.786
-THEN IT'S A DATE?

14:34.917 --> 14:36.963
-SURE, IT'S A DATE. YEAH.

14:37.093 --> 14:38.834
-YOU'RE ON. SEE YA.

14:39.400 --> 14:40.575
-SEE YA.

14:42.011 --> 14:47.495
-[PEACEFUL MUSIC]

15:09.821 --> 15:11.475
-GOOD NEWS.

15:12.737 --> 15:14.609
-WHAT'D THEY DO EXTEND DAYLIGHT
SAVINGS TIME YEAR-ROUND?

15:14.739 --> 15:16.785
THAT'S A GOOD
JOKE FOR THE ACT.

15:17.612 --> 15:19.875
-NO, WE TALKED TO THE
GALAXY CONTEST OFFICIALS.

15:20.006 --> 15:23.052
-AND THEY THINK YOU'D MAKE
A GREAT MASTER OF CEREMONIES.

15:23.879 --> 15:25.011
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

15:25.141 --> 15:27.013
-GOOD.
-GOOD! [GIGGLING]

15:27.143 --> 15:28.318
-THERE ARE SOME PERKS.

15:28.449 --> 15:29.276
-LIKE WHAT?

15:30.233 --> 15:31.539
-WARDROBE?

15:31.669 --> 15:32.540
-LIMOUSINE?

15:34.281 --> 15:35.586
-MANICURIST?

15:35.717 --> 15:37.153
-MASSEUSE?

15:37.762 --> 15:40.940
-IT'S THE COST OF BEING A
GOD, LIKE GEORGE HAMILTON.

15:46.423 --> 15:48.948
-TWO-NINE-FIVE TO SCARAB
ONE, WE NEED BACKUP

15:49.078 --> 15:50.906
OFF CHINA COVE REEF.

15:51.037 --> 15:53.082
GLASS BOTTOM BOAT
PULLING A TITANIC.

15:53.213 --> 15:54.823
CAN YOU ASSIST?

15:54.954 --> 15:57.130
-SCARAB ONE CREW: AFFIRMATIVE,
I'M TWO MILES SOUTHEAST.

15:57.260 --> 15:59.219
HI-HO SILVER, AWAY.

16:01.221 --> 16:02.787
HEY, MANNY, HOW YOU DOING?

16:05.007 --> 16:07.227
-HEY, MANNY, YOU KNOW,
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE

16:07.357 --> 16:09.577
IN THAT WHEELCHAIR DOESN'T
MEAN YOU HAVE TO STOP LIVING.

16:10.795 --> 16:13.494
I CAN TEACH YOU HOW TO WORK
THIS BEAST IN FIVE MINUTES.

16:14.277 --> 16:15.626
COME ON, GIVE IT A SHOT.

16:22.024 --> 16:27.769
-[TENSE MUSIC]

16:35.777 --> 16:37.431
-NOT MUCH OF
A TURNOUT, HUH?

16:37.561 --> 16:41.087
-NO. HOW DO YOU MAKE
COLLECTING TRASH FUN?

16:46.527 --> 16:48.007
-I HAVE AN IDEA.

16:49.486 --> 16:50.792
-I LIKE IT.
-YOU DO?

16:51.619 --> 16:53.969
-ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU
EVERYONE FOR SHOWING UP

16:54.100 --> 16:56.624
TO THE 10TH ANNUAL
PADI PROJECT AWARE

16:56.754 --> 16:58.887
UNDERWATER TRASH PICKUP.

16:59.018 --> 17:01.020
CAN YOU GATHER ALL YOUR
STUFF, AND WE'LL HEAD ON DOWN

17:01.150 --> 17:02.499
TO THE WATER.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.109
-MEET YOU DOWN THERE.

17:05.023 --> 17:07.590
-[LAUGHING] THAT'S GOOD.

17:07.722 --> 17:08.983
-NEWMIE: HELLO.

17:09.115 --> 17:10.594
-HEY, NEWMIE, MY
MAN. HOW'S IT GOING?

17:11.160 --> 17:13.118
-GOOD. DID YOU HAVE
A GOOD TIME TODAY?

17:13.249 --> 17:14.816
-TERRIFIC, YEAH IT WAS FUN.

17:14.945 --> 17:17.732
-LISTEN, I WAS THINKING
MAYBE YOU AND I COULD GO OUT

17:17.862 --> 17:19.994
AND GET BEER AND A BITE TO
EAT AFTER WORK TOMORROW?

17:20.126 --> 17:22.867
-SURE, SOUNDS GOOD. JUST
TELL ME WHERE AND WHEN.

17:22.998 --> 17:24.565
-WELL, WHERE IS A SECRET,

17:24.694 --> 17:26.306
BUT HOW ABOUT I PICK
YOU UP AT SEVEN?

17:26.958 --> 17:27.915
-SEVEN IT IS.

17:28.047 --> 17:29.526
-COOL. SEE YOU LATER.

17:29.657 --> 17:30.919
BYE, MITCH.

17:32.268 --> 17:34.792
-SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WHEN HE MAKES HIS BIG MOVE?

17:34.923 --> 17:36.185
-MOVE? WHO?

17:36.316 --> 17:37.230
-NEWMIE.

17:37.926 --> 17:39.319
-OH, VERY FUNNY.

17:39.449 --> 17:40.711
YOU KNOW NEWMIE AND
I ARE JUST FRIENDS.

17:40.842 --> 17:42.191
-WELL, YOU AND I
MIGHT THINK THAT,

17:42.322 --> 17:45.368
BUT HE HAS QUOTE-UNQUOTE
"THE HOTS" FOR YOU.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.241
-THE HOTS? YOU MEAN LIKE--

17:48.850 --> 17:50.286
-YEP, THOSE HOTS.

17:51.374 --> 17:52.723
-THIS IS NOT GOOD.

17:52.854 --> 17:55.291
-WHAT'S WORSE, HE THINKS
YOU HAVE THE HOTS FOR HIM.

17:55.944 --> 17:57.337
-ME AND NEWMIE, THE HOTS?

17:58.207 --> 18:01.254
-YES, YES, AND YES.

18:01.384 --> 18:03.865
-OH DEAR GOD.

18:05.214 --> 18:06.781
[SIGHS]

18:09.305 --> 18:11.829
-TWO-ONE-FOUR, THIS IS
TWO-NINE-FIVE, CAN YOU RESPOND

18:11.960 --> 18:14.093
TO HELP OUT AT
TOWER 12 OR NOT?

18:14.223 --> 18:15.746
-RESPONDING LIFEGUARD:
RESPOND TO WHAT?

18:15.877 --> 18:17.792
-I JUST CALLED YOU A MINUTE
AGO, I PUT YOU ON HOLD.

18:17.922 --> 18:19.402
-RESPONDING LIFEGUARD:
NO YOU DIDN'T.

18:22.013 --> 18:24.103
-THIS IS TWO-NINE-FIVE, DID
I JUST CALL YOU A MINUTE AGO?

18:24.233 --> 18:26.322
-RESPONDING LIFEGUARD: ME? NO.

18:29.412 --> 18:31.458
-THIS IS TWO-NINE-FIVE,
WHO'S THIS?

18:31.588 --> 18:32.763
-RESPONDING LIFEGUARD:
IT'S ME AGAIN, MANNY.
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

18:32.894 --> 18:33.982
-DAMN IT!

18:34.113 --> 18:35.157
-HEY, HEY, HEY,
TAKE IT EASY.

18:35.288 --> 18:36.637
WHAT'S THE MATTER, HERE?

18:36.767 --> 18:38.291
-I CAN'T GET THE
SWITCHBOARD TO WORK RIGHT.

18:38.421 --> 18:39.944
-JUST GIVE IT SOME TIME,
YOU'LL GET THE HANG OF IT.

18:40.075 --> 18:41.729
-WHAT IF I DON'T,
HUH MITCH?

18:41.859 --> 18:43.948
WHAT AM I GONNA DO, I
CAN'T DO ANYTHING ELSE.

18:44.079 --> 18:47.604
-MANNY, DON'T BEAT YOURSELF
UP, IT TAKES TIME TO ADJUST.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.172
-I USED TO BE A
LIFEGUARD, MITCH.

18:50.912 --> 18:53.871
NOW I'M JUST A TEMP WORKER,
AND I CAN'T DO ANYTHING RIGHT.

18:54.698 --> 18:59.094
-[SOLEMN MUSIC]

19:18.722 --> 19:20.071
-EXCUSE ME, I--

19:21.508 --> 19:22.987
I FOUND HIM, THANK YOU.

19:26.295 --> 19:27.296
HEY.

19:34.390 --> 19:35.870
WE BOTH KNOW I'M HERE.

19:39.308 --> 19:41.745
AW COME ON, MANNY, I
LOOKED EVERYWHERE FOR YOU.

19:41.876 --> 19:44.226
-I'VE BEEN HERE WITH
ALL THE OTHER REJECTS.

19:46.533 --> 19:47.621
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:48.578 --> 19:50.928
-I'M ONLINE,
GOT SOME EMAIL.

19:51.494 --> 19:54.323
THERE'S THIS GUY IN HAWAII I
MET THROUGH AMERICA ONLINE,

19:54.454 --> 19:55.672
HE'S A PARAPLEGIC TOO.

19:56.543 --> 19:59.546
-REALLY? WHAT DO
YOU GUYS TALK ABOUT?

20:00.460 --> 20:02.549
-TALK ABOUT THINGS
WE CAN'T DO ANYMORE.

20:02.679 --> 20:03.811
-OH FOR GOD'S SAKE.

20:03.941 --> 20:05.595
YOU KNOW WHAT, I'M
SORRY, I CAN'T.

20:05.726 --> 20:07.075
-HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:07.206 --> 20:08.511
-I'M LOW ON SELF-PITY
RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

20:08.642 --> 20:11.035
HERE'S ME IN YOUR FACE.
YOU'RE BEING RUDE.

20:12.123 --> 20:12.994
-WHAT DO YOU
WANT FROM ME?

20:15.039 --> 20:16.780
-YOU KNOW, I KNEW THIS
LITTLE KID ONCE, YOU KNOW.

20:16.911 --> 20:20.480
A REAL SPUNKY GUY, REAL BIG
SMILE, REAL POSITIVE ATTITUDE.

20:20.610 --> 20:21.916
YOU KNOW WHAT HE SAID?

20:22.046 --> 20:23.700
HE SAID HE WANTED
TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

20:23.831 --> 20:25.833
HE SAID HE WANTED TO BE A
LIFEGUARD MORE THAN ANYTHING

20:25.963 --> 20:28.923
IN THE WORLD AND THAT NOTHING
WOULD STAND IN HIS WAY.

20:29.053 --> 20:31.055
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT, NOTHING DID.

20:31.186 --> 20:32.927
-YEAH WELL, HE'S CHANGED.

20:33.057 --> 20:34.972
-I DON'T LIKE HIM
VERY MUCH ANYMORE.

20:36.278 --> 20:37.845
-WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GET OFF MY BACK, MITCH!

20:37.975 --> 20:40.543
-YOU GOTTA LIVE YOUR LIFE,
WHETHER YOU LIKE IT OR NOT.

20:41.544 --> 20:43.416
WHY DON'T YOU CONCENTRATE
ON THE THINGS YOU CAN DO

20:43.546 --> 20:45.592
INSTEAD OF CRYING OVER
THE THINGS YOU CAN'T.

20:46.245 --> 20:48.377
YOU WANT ME TO GET OFF
YOUR BACK, FINE I'M OFF IT.

20:48.508 --> 20:50.510
WHY DON'T YOU GET
OFF YOUR BACK?

20:50.640 --> 20:56.080
-[SOLEMN MUSIC]

21:13.794 --> 21:14.708
-HEY.

21:18.581 --> 21:19.669
WHAT'S THIS?

21:19.800 --> 21:21.280
-IT'S MY JOB APPLICATION.

21:27.547 --> 21:29.026
-IT'S ALL COMPUTER STUFF.

21:29.157 --> 21:32.595
-YEAH, I'VE BEEN TALKING TO
THE SPECIAL NEEDS DEPARTMENT

21:32.726 --> 21:33.770
AT IBM.

21:34.380 --> 21:35.946
AND THEY HELPED ME
COME UP WITH THE PLAN.

21:36.469 --> 21:37.557
-WHAT'S THE PLAN?

21:37.687 --> 21:41.038
-TO BRING BAYWATCH
INTO THE 21ST CENTURY.

21:41.169 --> 21:44.564
I WANT TO COMPUTERIZE
THAT DINOSAUR SWITCHBOARD,

21:44.694 --> 21:46.435
AND I WANT TO PUT
LAPTOPS AND CAMERAS

21:46.566 --> 21:48.002
ON EVERY SINGLE
LIFEGUARD TOWER.

21:48.132 --> 21:49.830
AND I WANT TO CONNECT
IT ALL TO A MOTHERBOARD

21:49.960 --> 21:51.179
HERE AT HEADQUARTERS.

21:52.485 --> 21:53.268
-CAMERAS?

21:53.399 --> 21:55.052
-EYES IN THE SKY.

21:55.705 --> 21:59.187
OUTSIDE OF HEADQUARTERS AND
ON KEY LIFEGUARD TOWERS.

22:00.362 --> 22:02.408
I COULD SEE PROBLEMS
ON THE BEACH.

22:02.538 --> 22:05.062
AND I COULD TELL THE LIFEGUARDS
WHERE THOSE PROBLEMS ARE AT.

22:05.193 --> 22:06.194
-"I," MEANING?

22:06.325 --> 22:07.848
-ME.

22:07.978 --> 22:10.067
LOOK, THIS IS SOMETHING
I CAN DO, MITCH.

22:11.068 --> 22:12.156
LET ME DO IT, PLEASE.

22:17.553 --> 22:22.428
-MANNY, THIS IS AWESOME.

22:22.558 --> 22:24.386
I MEAN IT'S GREAT,
BUT THIS IS EXPENSIVE.

22:25.474 --> 22:28.434
-IBM WILL SUPPLY THE
EQUIPMENT IF WE TEST THE SYSTEM

22:28.564 --> 22:29.391
HERE AT BAYWATCH.

22:40.271 --> 22:42.491
-YOU'RE BACK ON THE
PAYROLL, LIFEGUARD.

22:44.928 --> 22:50.238
-[TENSE MUSIC]

23:09.039 --> 23:10.780
-ANNOUNCER: HELLO
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

23:10.911 --> 23:15.568
WELCOME TO THE 7TH ANNUAL MISS
GALAXY FITNESS COMPETITION

23:15.698 --> 23:19.354
STAGED RIGHT HERE AT
BEAUTIFUL REDONDO BEACH.

23:26.970 --> 23:28.711
-APRIL: THAT'S
GREAT, GEORGE.

23:29.712 --> 23:31.540
-MY LEFT SIDE MIGHT BE
A LITTLE BETTER, HUH?

23:32.149 --> 23:34.238
-HEY, CAN YOU GIRLS MOVE A
LITTLE BIT CLOSER TO GEORGE?

23:34.369 --> 23:35.762
-SURE.
-OH YEAH, COME ON.

23:35.892 --> 23:36.937
-OKAY, HOW'S THIS?

23:37.067 --> 23:37.590
-GOOD, HUH?
-WILL THIS WORK?

23:37.720 --> 23:39.026
-YEAH, PERFECT.

23:39.156 --> 23:40.897
-YOU GETTING A
FLARE FROM THE TEETH?

23:47.469 --> 23:49.863
OKAY, THAT'S IT, GIRLS.
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR NOW.

23:51.430 --> 23:52.387
-WHERE ARE YOU
GOING, GEORGE?

23:52.518 --> 23:53.301
-MASSAGE.

23:53.432 --> 23:54.737
-MASSAGE?

23:54.868 --> 23:56.391
-MASSAGE, IT'S IN
THE LIST. MASSAGE.

23:56.522 --> 23:57.392
-YEAH, BUT WE STILL
HAVE THE SWIMSUIT PORTION

23:57.523 --> 23:59.525
OF THE COMPETITION.

23:59.655 --> 24:00.395
NOT TO MENTION, THE
PRESS CONFERENCE FOR
LAST YEAR'S WINNER.

24:00.526 --> 24:01.831
-HOSTING GETS ME TENSE.

24:01.962 --> 24:03.180
IT'S NOT EASY BEING
GEORGE HAMILTON.

24:03.311 --> 24:04.486
TA-TA.

24:10.013 --> 24:11.362
GROOVIN', BABY.

24:14.322 --> 24:15.366
-GREAT.

24:16.367 --> 24:21.677
-[CHEERFUL ROCK MUSIC]

24:36.605 --> 24:40.000
