♪ SWEET SWEET SUMMER
♪ COME ON AND TELL ME

26:36.638 --> 26:40.468
♪ WHY DO YOU FEEL SO GOOD
♪ WHY DO YOU FEEL SO GOOD

26:40.599 --> 26:42.731
♪ COME ON BABY YEAH

26:44.341 --> 26:47.606
♪ HOW COME YOU FEEL SO GOOD

26:47.736 --> 26:50.783
♪ HOW COME YOU FEEL SO GOOD

27:20.247 --> 27:21.074
-HOLD ON RIGHT THERE.

27:22.641 --> 27:23.511
-SURE.

27:25.948 --> 27:27.254
-NEWMIE: WE'RE HERE.

27:27.384 --> 27:28.821
-WHERE?

27:28.951 --> 27:30.300
-NEWMIE: THE SECRET
SPOT I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

27:30.431 --> 27:33.869
-I THOUGHT THAT WE WERE
JUST GONNA HAVE A BEER

27:34.000 --> 27:35.001
AND A BITE TO EAT.

27:35.131 --> 27:37.220
-WELL, WE ARE, FIGURATIVELY.

27:37.351 --> 27:39.875
-RIGHT. YOU KNOW, IN A
RESTAURANT WITH A LOT OF PEOPLE

27:40.006 --> 27:41.834
AROUND US, THAT
KIND OF THING.

27:41.964 --> 27:47.578
-NO, JUST ARMAND AND US.

27:50.059 --> 27:50.930
-ARMAND?

27:51.060 --> 27:51.887
-ARMAND.

27:52.018 --> 27:53.106
COME ON.

27:54.150 --> 27:57.676
THIS IS ONE OF MY MOST FAVORITE
SPOTS ON THE ENTIRE COAST.

27:57.806 --> 28:00.809
JUST A ROMANTIC BEACH,
BEAUTIFUL SUNSETS.

28:01.941 --> 28:05.684
AND THE VIEWS, OH IT'S
ABSOLUTELY MAGNIFICENT.

28:06.772 --> 28:09.818
-ALEX: IT'S
BEAUTIFUL, BUT NEWMAN--

28:11.864 --> 28:13.648
-I LOVE THE VIEW, DON'T YOU?

28:13.779 --> 28:15.084
-YEAH, IT'S GREAT.

28:15.215 --> 28:16.042
-HERE.

28:16.172 --> 28:16.956
-I'LL JUST--

28:17.086 --> 28:18.609
-OH! HERE, COME.

28:22.222 --> 28:24.180
DUCK A L'ORANGE.

28:24.877 --> 28:26.356
-I BEG YOUR PARDON?

28:26.487 --> 28:27.662
-IT'S WHAT WE'RE
HAVING FOR DINNER.

28:28.489 --> 28:31.448
HOLD ON JUST A SECOND, I
NEED TO CHECK WITH ARMAND.

28:34.756 --> 28:36.932
-[GROANING]

28:37.063 --> 28:38.238
OKAY.

28:47.073 --> 28:48.161
-[PHONE RINGING]

28:48.291 --> 28:49.118
-BUCHANNON.

28:49.249 --> 28:50.816
-MITCH, HELP.

28:50.946 --> 28:52.469
-MITCH: WHAT'S WRONG?

28:52.600 --> 28:54.123
-IT'S NEWMIE, HE'S GETTING
READY TO MAKE HIS MOVE.

28:55.734 --> 28:57.300
-HOW DO YOU KNOW?

28:57.431 --> 28:59.607
-BECAUSE WE'RE ON THE
BEACH, ALONE, WITH ARMAND,

28:59.738 --> 29:01.652
AND HE'S MAKING
DUCK A L'ORANGE.

29:01.783 --> 29:04.917
-ALEX, WHAT DO
YOU WANT ME TO DO?

29:05.047 --> 29:06.788
-I WANT YOU TO COME
HAVE DINNER WITH US,

29:06.919 --> 29:07.963
BECAUSE IF YOU'RE HERE,
HE WON'T DO ANYTHING.

29:08.094 --> 29:09.443
I NEED A CHAPERONE.

29:09.573 --> 29:11.140
-OH FOR GOD'S SAKE,
YOU'RE A BIG GIRL.

29:11.706 --> 29:14.361
-PLEASE? I DON'T WANT
TO HURT HIS FEELINGS.

29:14.491 --> 29:16.276
IF YOU'RE HERE, HE
WON'T DO ANYTHING.

29:16.406 --> 29:19.409
-ALEX, YOU KNOW WHAT
THEY SAY, "TWO'S COMPANY."

29:20.367 --> 29:24.806
-POINT DOOM, GET HERE OR I
WILL NEVER SPEAK TO YOU AGAIN.

29:40.082 --> 29:41.301
-HELLO.

29:41.431 --> 29:42.693
-[ALEX CHUCKLES]

29:42.824 --> 29:44.652
-YOU KNOW, THIS VIEW
IS SO ROMANTIC.

29:45.261 --> 29:47.916
I DIDN'T WANT YOU TO
MISS A MOMENT OF IT.

29:48.047 --> 29:50.005
LET ME JUST GET MY CHAIR
AND MOVE IT AROUND.

29:58.318 --> 30:01.234
DID YOU LIKE ARMAND'S
DUCK A L'ORANGE?

30:01.364 --> 30:03.062
-OH, IT WAS SUPERB, I
REALLY APPRECIATE YOU

30:03.192 --> 30:04.150
GOING THROUGH
ALL THIS TROUBLE.

30:05.542 --> 30:07.762
-ARMAND, I THINK WE'RE
DONE WITH OUR COURSE.

30:07.893 --> 30:08.676
COULD YOU TAKE THE PLATES?

30:08.807 --> 30:09.677
-YES, SIR.

30:10.286 --> 30:12.027
-ALEX: THANK YOU, ARMAND.

30:12.158 --> 30:13.855
-THANK YOU VERY MUCH, AND I
THINK WE SHOULD HAVE A TOAST

30:13.986 --> 30:15.944
TO THE MOST BEAUTIFUL WOMAN
ON THE MOST ROMANTIC BEACH--

30:16.075 --> 30:17.424
-OH, MITCH!

30:18.338 --> 30:21.471
-NO, THAT'S A CAR ON THE
HIGHWAY. THAT'S NOT MITCH.

30:25.954 --> 30:27.913
TO THE MOST BEAUTIFUL WOMAN
ON THE MOST ROMANTIC BEACH--

30:28.043 --> 30:29.305
-OH LOOK, THERE'S MITCH.

30:32.395 --> 30:34.049
-NO, THAT'S A WOMAN
ON THAT SEA-DOO.

30:36.399 --> 30:37.661
-YOU'RE RIGHT.

30:43.058 --> 30:46.670
-TO THE MOST BEAUTIFUL WOMAN
ON THE MOST ROMANTIC BEACH--

30:46.801 --> 30:48.585
-HEY, MITCH! THERE HE IS.

30:48.716 --> 30:50.457
-WHY DO YOU
KEEP SAYING THAT?

30:54.853 --> 30:56.855
-HEY, MITCH! HEY!

30:56.985 --> 30:58.987
-HEY, ALEX. HEY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

30:59.118 --> 31:00.380
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

31:00.510 --> 31:02.295
-I'M DOING A
LITTLE SURF FISHING.

31:02.425 --> 31:03.557
-WELL, WHY HERE?

31:03.687 --> 31:05.428
WHY NOT UP THERE
OR DOWN THERE?

31:05.559 --> 31:07.039
OR HOW ABOUT MEXICO?

31:07.169 --> 31:08.954
-I GUESS WE FOUND YOUR
LITTLE SECRET SPOT, HUH?

31:09.084 --> 31:10.520
-WELL I GUESS IT'S
NO SECRET ANYMORE.

31:10.651 --> 31:11.478
-NOPE.

31:12.783 --> 31:14.394
-OH, HAVING A LITTLE
DINNER, ARE WE?

31:14.524 --> 31:16.744
-YES, WE ARE HAVING
DUCK A L'ORANGE.

31:16.875 --> 31:18.354
WOULD YOU LIKE TO JOIN US?
WE STILL HAVE SOME LEFT.

31:18.485 --> 31:20.139
-NO, YOU STAY, HOW OFTEN
DO YOU GET A CHANCE?

31:20.269 --> 31:22.576
-[EXCITED CROSS-TALK]

31:22.706 --> 31:24.056
-GUYS, GUYS TAKE IT EASY.

31:24.186 --> 31:27.450
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT, I'M
GONNA CONTINUE TO FISH

31:27.581 --> 31:29.757
BUT RIGHT DOWN
THERE, OKAY?

31:29.888 --> 31:32.716
YOU GUYS FINISH YOUR DINNER
AND PRETEND I'M NOT EVEN HERE.

31:35.241 --> 31:36.633
-THANK YOU.
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

31:38.940 --> 31:40.115
-I WILL SAVE YOU DESSERT.

31:56.044 --> 31:57.524
NEWMIE--

31:57.654 --> 31:59.047
-MAYBE I WAS THINKING
AFTER DINNER WE COULD

31:59.178 --> 32:01.571
TAKE A DRIVE UP THE
COAST, WALK IN THE SAND,

32:01.702 --> 32:03.182
WATCH THE SUNSET.

32:03.312 --> 32:04.705
AND THEN, MAYBE COULD--
-NEWMAN, DON'T.

32:05.619 --> 32:06.707
-DON'T WHAT?

32:08.187 --> 32:11.668
-DON'T SAY ANYTHING,
DON'T DO ANYTHING.

32:13.366 --> 32:14.628
DON'T MAKE A MOVE.

32:16.282 --> 32:17.326
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

32:17.457 --> 32:19.328
-[SIGHS]

32:20.373 --> 32:24.072
LOOK, NEWMAN, YOU
ARE THE SWEETEST GUY.

32:24.203 --> 32:25.378
I MEAN, EVERYBODY LOVES YOU.

32:25.508 --> 32:28.381
AND I LIKE YOU
A TON, YOU KNOW,

32:28.511 --> 32:30.905
BUT NOT LIKE THAT.

32:32.602 --> 32:35.301
I HAVE HAD THE BEST TIME
HANGING OUT WITH YOU

32:35.431 --> 32:36.519
AND DOING STUFF.

32:37.564 --> 32:41.785
NEWMIE, YOU AND
I, WE'RE BUDDIES.

32:42.961 --> 32:44.963
GOOD BUDDIES ARE HARD
TO FIND, YOU KNOW.

32:45.920 --> 32:49.097
AND I WAS JUST THINKING,

32:49.228 --> 32:51.447
THAT I REALLY DON'T
WANT TO MESS THAT UP.

32:52.927 --> 32:53.841
YOU UNDERSTAND?

32:54.842 --> 32:55.712
-YEAH.

32:57.540 --> 32:59.455
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT WE
SHOULD DO TO FIX THIS.

32:59.586 --> 33:00.935
-WHAT'S THAT?

33:01.066 --> 33:03.068
-LET'S STOP THIS
DATING THING.

33:03.851 --> 33:06.332
JUST HANG OUT TOGETHER
WHENEVER WE FEEL LIKE IT,

33:08.203 --> 33:09.074
LIKE BUDDIES DO.

33:09.813 --> 33:10.727
-LIKE BUDDIES.

33:12.120 --> 33:12.991
-BUDDIES.

33:15.471 --> 33:17.821
-YOU ARE SUCH THE MAN.

33:25.003 --> 33:29.442
-HEY! HEY, I
GOT ONE! [LAUGHS]

33:30.312 --> 33:34.447
-[LAUGHING]

33:39.060 --> 33:44.457
-[ACTION-PACKED MUSIC]

33:57.252 --> 34:00.908
-ANNOUNCER: ON YOUR
MARKS, GET SET, GO!

36:10.951 --> 36:16.304
-[CHEERING]

36:25.705 --> 36:27.881
-MANNY: TWO-NINE-FIVE
TO TOWER 12.

36:30.231 --> 36:31.841
-TOWER 12, MANNY.
WHAT'S UP?

36:31.972 --> 36:34.235
-YOU GOT SOME KIDS BEHIND
YOU UNLOADING THEIR CAR.

36:34.366 --> 36:36.281
THEY GOT A BARBECUE
AND A CASE OF BEER.

36:36.933 --> 36:38.718
-I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

36:48.423 --> 36:50.643
-MANNY: SCARAB TWO,
THIS TWO-NINE-FIVE.

36:50.773 --> 36:52.514
-SCARAB TWO LIFEGUARD:
SCARAB TWO. SEND YOUR TRAFFIC.

36:52.645 --> 36:54.473
-YOU'VE GOT A BEER REGATTA
GOING ON ABOUT A HUNDRED YARDS

36:54.603 --> 36:56.126
OFF THE JETTY.

36:56.257 --> 36:57.389
AND THERE'S A WAVE RUNNER
TAKING TARGET PRACTICE.

36:57.519 --> 36:58.738
-SCARAB TWO LIFEGUARD:
WORKING ON IT.

37:06.224 --> 37:08.791
-TOWER EIGHT, THIS
IS TWO-NINE-FIVE.

37:09.444 --> 37:10.880
-TOWER EIGHT: THIS IS
EIGHT, TWO-NINE-FIVE. COME IN.

37:11.011 --> 37:13.666
-THERE'S A GUY IN A TANK
TOP AND A BASEBALL HAT

37:13.796 --> 37:16.321
JUST NORTH OF YOUR TOWER
AND HE'S PICKING POCKETS.

37:16.451 --> 37:17.887
-TOWER EIGHT: I SEE HIM.

37:18.018 --> 37:19.715
-I'LL NOTIFY THE POLICE
WHILE YOU DETAIN HIM.

37:19.846 --> 37:21.413
-TOWER EIGHT:
THAT'S A ROGER.

37:25.068 --> 37:27.027
-WOW, THAT'S AWESOME.

37:27.157 --> 37:28.071
EVERYTHING WORKING?

37:28.202 --> 37:29.247
-YEAH, PERFECT.

37:30.465 --> 37:31.423
-WELCOME BACK TO BAYWATCH.

37:31.553 --> 37:32.554
GREAT TO HAVE YOU HERE.

37:32.685 --> 37:34.034
-THANKS, MITCH.

37:34.164 --> 37:35.122
HEY, THANKS FOR THE
KICK IN THE BUTT.

37:35.253 --> 37:37.646
-HEY, ANYTIME.

37:39.387 --> 37:40.562
-I KNOW.

37:43.043 --> 37:45.001
-HOST: HERE WE ARE
AT THE FINAL STAGES

37:45.132 --> 37:47.787
OF THE MISS
GALAXY COMPETITION.

37:47.917 --> 37:50.442
THESE JUDGES SURE HAVE A
HARD DECISION AHEAD OF THEM.

37:50.572 --> 37:54.141
SO LADIES, GIVE ONE LAST
CHANCE TO SHOW OFF YOUR STUFF

37:54.272 --> 37:57.275
BEFORE ADVANCING ON TO
THE INDIVIDUAL INTERVIEWS.

37:57.797 --> 38:02.976
-[CHEERING]

38:11.289 --> 38:16.642
AND NOW, ONCE AGAIN, OUR
CELEBRITY HOST, GEORGE HAMILTON.

38:22.648 --> 38:25.520
-THE GALAXY GIRLS, LADIES
AND GENTLEMEN. YES, SIR.

38:27.305 --> 38:31.004
LET'S HAVE A BIG HAND FOR
THEM, THE GALAXY GIRLS.

38:32.353 --> 38:36.792
WELL, THE OBSTACLE COURSE AND
SWIMWEAR COMPETITION ARE OVER.

38:36.923 --> 38:39.099
AND IT'S TIME FOR
THE WINNER'S CIRCLE.

38:39.229 --> 38:41.623
THIS FEATURES THE TOP
WOMEN, WHO ARE JUDGED

38:41.754 --> 38:44.974
BY THEIR OVERALL APPEARANCE,
BEAUTY, BODY TONE,

38:45.105 --> 38:46.454
POISE, CONFIDENCE, AND--

38:46.585 --> 38:47.803
CHERYL, COULD YOU
LIFT THE CARD?

38:47.934 --> 38:48.804
-OH.

38:48.935 --> 38:51.590
-CONFIDENCE AND
STAGE PRESENCE.

38:51.720 --> 38:55.550
EACH CONTESTANT WILL ANSWER
A PREDETERMINED QUESTION,

38:55.681 --> 38:57.726
AND THE FINAL DECISION
FROM THE JUDGES

38:57.857 --> 39:03.428
WILL DECIDE THIS
YEAR'S MISS GALAXY!

39:03.558 --> 39:06.213
YES, SIR! LET'S
HAVE A BIG HAND!

39:07.040 --> 39:08.607
FOR THE GALAXY GIRLS.

39:08.737 --> 39:12.959
BUT FIRST, A LOT OF PEOPLE
THINK GEORGE HAMILTON

39:13.089 --> 39:14.613
GOT A BIG HEAD.

39:14.743 --> 39:17.006
WELL, A LOT OF YOU DON'T
SEE HIM THE WAY I SEE HIM.

39:17.137 --> 39:19.400
AND I JUST WANT TO
DO SOMETHING FOR YOU,

39:19.531 --> 39:21.097
BECAUSE YOU'VE BEEN
A GREAT AUDIENCE.

39:21.228 --> 39:23.273
THE PRESS, HERE, IF YOU
WANT TO LEAVE A NUMBER,

39:23.404 --> 39:25.058
I'LL GIVE YOU A HEAD
SHEET AND MAYBE CALL.

39:25.188 --> 39:26.581
[CHUCKLES]

39:27.495 --> 39:29.323
-WELL THAT'S IT
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

39:29.454 --> 39:30.411
GOTTA LEAVE NOW.

39:30.542 --> 39:32.370
[CHUCKLES] OH, NO. NOT HERE.

39:32.500 --> 39:34.807
GOODBYE, ALL. THANK
YOU VERY MUCH.

39:35.547 --> 39:38.767
-APRIL AND JESSIE:
EARL! EARL!

39:41.901 --> 39:42.989
-COME BACK HERE!

39:43.119 --> 39:44.251
-WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

39:44.382 --> 39:45.644
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

39:52.781 --> 39:54.740
-I'M MICHAEL NEWMAN, A
PROFESSIONAL LIFEGUARD.

39:54.870 --> 39:57.351
THE OCEAN IS A FUN AND
EXCITING PLACE TO PLAY.

39:57.482 --> 39:59.135
BUT DON'T EVER
SWIM BY YOURSELF.

39:59.266 --> 40:00.572
ALWAYS HAVE A
BUDDY WITH YOU--

40:00.702 --> 40:02.530
-DIRECTOR: CUT, CUT,
CUT, CUT, CUT.

40:02.661 --> 40:05.315
THAT WAS GREAT.
AWESOME, PAUSE THE SET.

40:05.446 --> 40:06.752
COME ON OUT, OKAY, MARK?

40:06.882 --> 40:07.883
-THAT'S MIKE.

40:08.014 --> 40:10.799
-WHATEVER, I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT,

40:10.930 --> 40:12.497
I WANT TO TRY SOMETHING
NEW HERE, ALL RIGHT?

40:12.627 --> 40:16.849
SO, IT'S A WRAP. OKAY, MILT?

40:16.979 --> 40:18.416
-THAT'S MIKE.

40:18.546 --> 40:20.679
-OKAY, WHATEVER.
COOKIE, COME ON IN HERE.

40:25.771 --> 40:27.294
YOU'RE GREAT.

40:27.425 --> 40:30.210
HAS ANYONE EVER TOLD YOU
THAT YOU LOOK A LOT LIKE--

40:30.340 --> 40:32.342
-YEAH, I KNOW,
WARREN BEATTY.

40:35.433 --> 40:36.695
-DIRECTOR: COME
ON IN HERE, COOKIE.

40:36.825 --> 40:38.697
GET IN THE WATER, BEATTY.

40:38.827 --> 40:39.959
-GEORGE: GET IN THE WATER?

40:40.089 --> 40:41.482
BUT IT'S COLD.

40:41.613 --> 40:43.049
I DON'T HAVE TO MESS
UP MY HAIR, DO I?

40:45.443 --> 40:49.882
-[END THEME PLAYING]
